1
00:02:05,239 --> 00:02:06,560
Didn't I tell you

2
00:02:07,640 --> 00:02:09,280
not to talk to her

3
00:02:09,759 --> 00:02:11,479
as long as you're living here?

4
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:14,000
When I locked eyes with Nut earlier,

5
00:02:14,960 --> 00:02:17,280
-my heart was beating really fast.
-What?

6
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:21,000
You're just like him, Little Prince.

7
00:02:21,080 --> 00:02:23,439
You really care for me.

8
00:02:24,439 --> 00:02:26,680
Now that you know
I'm not related to Neung,

9
00:02:27,439 --> 00:02:29,319
you won't kick me out, will you?

10
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:31,319
If I wanted to,

11
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:33,319
I would've left you
at the temple that day.

12
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:35,360
I'm a bear, not a dog.

13
00:02:35,919 --> 00:02:37,840
Listen. He's just a kid.

14
00:02:38,439 --> 00:02:41,879
Haven't you heard people say
that you should never work with kids?

15
00:02:41,960 --> 00:02:43,560
If you don't trust me…

16
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:48,800
you could try going out with me.

17
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:15,560
Everyone, look.

18
00:03:16,919 --> 00:03:20,000
Teddy is acting
more and more like a human.

19
00:03:21,719 --> 00:03:22,680
How?

20
00:03:22,759 --> 00:03:24,800
You seem to have a lot on your mind,

21
00:03:24,879 --> 00:03:26,919
like there's something you want to say

22
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:28,719
but you won't say it.

23
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:31,680
You used to say all your thoughts
when you were a teddy bear.

24
00:03:32,840 --> 00:03:35,039
I guess the more time I spend with humans,

25
00:03:36,280 --> 00:03:39,080
the more I know that
there are some things we shouldn't say,

26
00:03:39,639 --> 00:03:41,360
because they can hurt someone.

27
00:03:43,639 --> 00:03:45,560
But some things, I just don't understand,

28
00:03:46,680 --> 00:03:48,120
so I don't know what to say.

29
00:03:48,639 --> 00:03:52,439
If being a human is so hard,
turn back into a teddy bear.

30
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:53,879
Come back to us.

31
00:03:54,919 --> 00:03:56,439
I'm trying.

32
00:03:57,439 --> 00:04:00,319
I almost found out who gave me to Nut,

33
00:04:01,520 --> 00:04:03,039
but I was still wrong.

34
00:04:03,719 --> 00:04:07,879
Maybe Nut won you
after playing darts at a temple fair?

35
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:10,159
No!

36
00:04:10,719 --> 00:04:12,759
He said someone important gave me to him.

37
00:04:12,840 --> 00:04:15,000
I must be more important
than a prize at a fair.

38
00:04:15,479 --> 00:04:16,920
Calm down, Tofu.

39
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:21,040
Look, he gets angry
like a real person now.

40
00:04:21,120 --> 00:04:24,959
-He's kind of similar to Nut.
-He's kind of similar to Nut.

41
00:04:45,879 --> 00:04:47,079
Hey!

42
00:04:49,279 --> 00:04:50,240
Why are you here?

43
00:04:52,439 --> 00:04:54,000
I brought in your laundry.

44
00:04:54,879 --> 00:04:56,360
What should I do next?

45
00:04:57,519 --> 00:04:59,199
You need to go and iron them.

46
00:05:00,319 --> 00:05:02,000
-Iron?
-Yes.

47
00:05:04,720 --> 00:05:06,839
Don't tell me you don't know how to do it.

48
00:05:11,360 --> 00:05:12,600
Listen.

49
00:05:12,680 --> 00:05:14,160
This is linen,

50
00:05:14,680 --> 00:05:15,680
so it needs high heat.

51
00:05:16,160 --> 00:05:18,800
Put the heat on high for linen.

52
00:05:19,680 --> 00:05:21,079
Then start ironing.

53
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:25,680
Go slowly, see?

54
00:05:27,879 --> 00:05:29,040
Go over the whole thing.

55
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:32,480
That's it.

56
00:05:34,040 --> 00:05:36,160
You try this side.

57
00:05:43,639 --> 00:05:44,639
Slowly.

58
00:05:45,120 --> 00:05:46,240
Yes.

59
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:51,000
Don't iron over the buttons.

60
00:05:52,199 --> 00:05:53,279
Here.

61
00:05:53,360 --> 00:05:54,480
What you do

62
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:58,079
is gently push the iron
between the buttons like this.

63
00:05:58,759 --> 00:06:00,079
Slowly.

64
00:06:02,720 --> 00:06:03,639
See?

65
00:06:04,360 --> 00:06:05,279
Yes.

66
00:06:06,319 --> 00:06:07,160
Try it.

67
00:06:09,759 --> 00:06:10,600
Here.

68
00:06:17,120 --> 00:06:18,959
Oh, Tofu.

69
00:06:22,879 --> 00:06:24,079
Here.

70
00:06:24,160 --> 00:06:25,800
Like this, slowly.

71
00:06:36,319 --> 00:06:38,759
Hold the fabric with one hand.

72
00:06:38,839 --> 00:06:39,879
Yes.

73
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:24,680
Nut, are you hurt?

74
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:30,120
No,

75
00:07:30,199 --> 00:07:31,279
it's just hot.

76
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:34,399
Was it hot?

77
00:07:34,480 --> 00:07:36,079
Touch your earlobes.

78
00:07:37,279 --> 00:07:38,319
Is it better?

79
00:07:39,639 --> 00:07:41,000
A little bit.

80
00:07:43,240 --> 00:07:44,560
Hold your earlobes.

81
00:07:44,639 --> 00:07:45,839
What for?

82
00:07:45,920 --> 00:07:47,720
Just do as I say.

83
00:07:48,639 --> 00:07:49,519
No.

84
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:52,000
-Like this.
-No.

85
00:07:52,079 --> 00:07:53,319
Like this.

86
00:08:25,120 --> 00:08:26,920
It's all right, it's not hot anymore.

87
00:08:30,560 --> 00:08:32,440
Why do I feel so hot?

88
00:08:38,120 --> 00:08:40,679
Is this the sound of my heart or yours?

89
00:08:43,799 --> 00:08:45,639
Get out. You're not good.

90
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:48,799
I'll do it myself. Go.

91
00:08:50,120 --> 00:08:51,120
Go on.

92
00:09:43,840 --> 00:09:44,879
Beary,

93
00:09:44,960 --> 00:09:47,840
why are you all hot and sweaty?

94
00:09:50,960 --> 00:09:52,360
I was ironing.

95
00:09:52,840 --> 00:09:54,320
Maybe it gave me fever.

96
00:09:54,399 --> 00:09:56,720
Can ironing cause fever?

97
00:09:57,840 --> 00:09:58,679
Right?

98
00:09:58,759 --> 00:10:01,639
Tell me how you feel.

99
00:10:03,759 --> 00:10:05,080
I'm not sure.

100
00:10:07,679 --> 00:10:09,120
I feel hot all over.

101
00:10:11,440 --> 00:10:13,080
There are butterflies in my stomach.

102
00:10:16,200 --> 00:10:17,679
My heart is beating fast too.

103
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:20,960
You don't sound like you have fever.

104
00:10:21,039 --> 00:10:24,120
Oh, he can't understand you.

105
00:10:24,799 --> 00:10:25,960
Hey, Tofu,

106
00:10:26,039 --> 00:10:27,000
are you sure

107
00:10:27,080 --> 00:10:30,000
that the only thing you did was iron?

108
00:10:31,200 --> 00:10:32,840
It really was.

109
00:10:33,919 --> 00:10:36,039
But while I was ironing,

110
00:10:36,120 --> 00:10:38,039
Nut said he was hot,

111
00:10:38,960 --> 00:10:40,840
so I held his earlobes.

112
00:10:41,759 --> 00:10:43,519
-Held his earlobes?
-Held his earlobes?

113
00:10:43,600 --> 00:10:45,720
Did you hold anything else?

114
00:10:46,679 --> 00:10:47,759
No.

115
00:10:55,600 --> 00:10:58,960
You did just that and then got all hot?

116
00:10:59,799 --> 00:11:02,559
Ha, what do single people know?

117
00:11:02,639 --> 00:11:04,440
Little One, tell them.

118
00:11:05,039 --> 00:11:08,720
I think you like Nut, Tofu.

119
00:11:09,240 --> 00:11:11,039
That's why your heart beats fast

120
00:11:11,120 --> 00:11:14,159
and you get butterflies
when you're near him.

121
00:11:15,960 --> 00:11:18,720
It's that feeling you get
when you really like someone.

122
00:11:19,279 --> 00:11:21,120
When you're near them

123
00:11:21,720 --> 00:11:23,399
and lock eyes with them,

124
00:11:23,480 --> 00:11:24,919
your heart starts beating fast.

125
00:11:28,879 --> 00:11:30,759
But I'm just a teddy bear.

126
00:11:31,240 --> 00:11:33,320
How can I like my owner?

127
00:11:33,399 --> 00:11:34,960
Don't forget, Beary,

128
00:11:35,039 --> 00:11:38,200
you're not just a teddy bear anymore.

129
00:11:38,759 --> 00:11:41,200
But I have to turn back
into a teddy bear anyway.

130
00:12:06,279 --> 00:12:08,960
I don't know
when I'll turn back into a teddy bear,

131
00:12:10,039 --> 00:12:11,759
but I've decided that

132
00:12:12,480 --> 00:12:13,799
before that day comes,

133
00:12:14,639 --> 00:12:17,120
I'll make the most of my time with Nut.

134
00:12:32,200 --> 00:12:33,480
Nut, are you hurt?

135
00:12:37,559 --> 00:12:38,840
No,

136
00:12:38,919 --> 00:12:39,960
it's just hot.

137
00:12:40,039 --> 00:12:41,480
Hold your earlobes.

138
00:12:41,559 --> 00:12:42,759
What for?

139
00:12:42,840 --> 00:12:44,600
Just do as I say.

140
00:12:45,799 --> 00:12:46,759
-Like this.
-No.

141
00:12:46,840 --> 00:12:48,120
Like this.

142
00:13:00,679 --> 00:13:02,360
Why do I feel so hot?

143
00:13:08,080 --> 00:13:10,519
Is this the sound of my heart or yours?

144
00:13:42,600 --> 00:13:43,559
I'll be off, Mom.

145
00:13:43,639 --> 00:13:45,039
Nut.

146
00:13:48,480 --> 00:13:49,919
It's my first time making it.

147
00:13:50,519 --> 00:13:52,039
It might not be very good.

148
00:13:56,639 --> 00:13:58,799
By the way, how's the shirt?

149
00:14:04,240 --> 00:14:05,320
Oh,

150
00:14:05,399 --> 00:14:06,320
where's Mom?

151
00:14:07,799 --> 00:14:08,879
Nut.

152
00:14:11,360 --> 00:14:13,679
I'm sorry, I overslept.

153
00:14:16,879 --> 00:14:18,320
Oh, and your lunch?

154
00:14:19,240 --> 00:14:20,559
I already made it for him.

155
00:14:22,320 --> 00:14:24,320
I'm off to work, Mom.

156
00:14:24,399 --> 00:14:25,919
You should go back to sleep.

157
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:30,000
Bye.

158
00:14:38,159 --> 00:14:40,399
I can't even wake up
to make lunch for Nut.

159
00:14:41,960 --> 00:14:44,679
How am I supposed to do
other things for him?

160
00:14:45,720 --> 00:14:47,399
Don't worry, Mrs. Na,

161
00:14:47,480 --> 00:14:49,080
anyone can oversleep.

162
00:14:49,720 --> 00:14:52,559
As long as you stay healthy,
Nut will be happy.

163
00:14:58,720 --> 00:15:00,039
Have some apple juice.

164
00:15:01,039 --> 00:15:03,200
Song's father said
it's good for the heart.

165
00:15:04,480 --> 00:15:06,279
I want you to try some.

166
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:09,200
Thank you.

167
00:15:13,679 --> 00:15:15,399
You're so lovely, Little Prince.

168
00:15:27,440 --> 00:15:28,840
I'm sorry, Mrs. Na.

169
00:15:30,320 --> 00:15:32,279
I made you oversleep.

170
00:15:39,120 --> 00:15:40,559
But if I didn't do this…

171
00:15:41,960 --> 00:15:43,840
Nut wouldn't be happy.

172
00:15:44,679 --> 00:15:46,240
Go on.

173
00:15:50,320 --> 00:15:51,759
What are you making?

174
00:15:52,679 --> 00:15:53,960
Apple juice.

175
00:15:54,039 --> 00:15:55,480
Thank you.

176
00:16:16,759 --> 00:16:18,519
FIRST LOVE

177
00:16:38,039 --> 00:16:39,480
It's my first time making it.

178
00:16:39,960 --> 00:16:41,320
It might not be very good.

179
00:16:56,399 --> 00:16:57,399
Want to try it?

180
00:16:58,320 --> 00:16:59,159
Yuck.

181
00:16:59,679 --> 00:17:02,080
Try it. I put a lot of effort into it.

182
00:17:02,159 --> 00:17:03,000
Here.

183
00:17:06,119 --> 00:17:07,119
How is it?

184
00:17:07,920 --> 00:17:08,880
Delicious, right?

185
00:17:09,440 --> 00:17:10,359
Hey,

186
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:12,319
it's great.

187
00:17:24,480 --> 00:17:26,960
Iced Americano with no sugar,

188
00:17:27,039 --> 00:17:29,920
but with all my heart,
in exchange for your lunch.

189
00:17:33,799 --> 00:17:36,200
How come your food looks terrible today?

190
00:17:36,279 --> 00:17:37,720
The pork is all burnt.

191
00:17:38,200 --> 00:17:39,960
There's no food for me today then.

192
00:17:40,440 --> 00:17:42,119
I'll throw it out for you.

193
00:17:42,839 --> 00:17:43,920
No,

194
00:17:44,440 --> 00:17:45,720
I can eat it.

195
00:17:57,160 --> 00:17:58,160
Gen,

196
00:18:00,880 --> 00:18:02,759
Nut's taste is so weird.

197
00:18:03,400 --> 00:18:05,759
He gives yummy-looking food
to other people,

198
00:18:05,839 --> 00:18:08,240
but eats burnt pork by himself.

199
00:18:10,599 --> 00:18:13,319
What's so special about that pork?

200
00:18:16,400 --> 00:18:19,480
If he can eat stuff like that,
all is not lost for me.

201
00:18:19,559 --> 00:18:20,920
I have an idea.

202
00:18:23,160 --> 00:18:24,160
You're crazy.

203
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:31,359
What's up?

204
00:18:32,920 --> 00:18:33,799
What?

205
00:18:33,880 --> 00:18:35,400
You bought an air fryer?

206
00:18:35,480 --> 00:18:36,319
Why?

207
00:18:36,400 --> 00:18:38,079
I'm going to learn to fry pork.

208
00:18:38,759 --> 00:18:41,200
I'll impress Nut with my cooking skills.

209
00:18:42,440 --> 00:18:44,640
You never cease to amaze me.

210
00:18:45,480 --> 00:18:47,640
I'll bring you some to try later.

211
00:18:47,720 --> 00:18:48,720
Bye now.

212
00:18:53,720 --> 00:18:54,720
Oh, Prib.

213
00:18:55,359 --> 00:18:56,519
Oh, Mr. Anik.

214
00:19:00,880 --> 00:19:02,880
Any updates on Tarn's case?

215
00:19:02,960 --> 00:19:05,839
The police
still haven't ruled out anything,

216
00:19:05,920 --> 00:19:09,599
for both the conflict with TRD
and his personal problems.

217
00:19:10,160 --> 00:19:11,880
In his personal life,

218
00:19:11,960 --> 00:19:14,880
I'm certain there's no woman involved.

219
00:19:16,039 --> 00:19:17,640
What makes you think so?

220
00:19:18,400 --> 00:19:21,079
Since he came back to Thailand
two years ago,

221
00:19:21,160 --> 00:19:22,839
he hasn't dated anyone.

222
00:19:22,920 --> 00:19:25,279
He never forgot his first love

223
00:19:25,359 --> 00:19:27,640
and he never got serious with anyone.

224
00:19:28,559 --> 00:19:31,079
I was really touched by that,

225
00:19:31,160 --> 00:19:33,519
so I created a page called

226
00:19:33,599 --> 00:19:35,759
"Once Upon Our Time" to tell his story.

227
00:19:36,240 --> 00:19:40,519
If you check it out,
you might understand him more.

228
00:19:43,519 --> 00:19:45,039
ONCE UPON OUR TIME

229
00:19:45,119 --> 00:19:47,880
I didn't know
that Tarn could never love me,

230
00:19:47,960 --> 00:19:49,960
so I made a move on him.

231
00:19:50,599 --> 00:19:53,599
In the end, I failed.

232
00:19:53,680 --> 00:19:56,039
We became good friends instead

233
00:19:56,599 --> 00:19:57,920
and grew a lot closer.

234
00:19:59,640 --> 00:20:03,880
After you've read the page, if you want
to know anything else about Tarn,

235
00:20:04,400 --> 00:20:05,680
you can ask me.

236
00:20:08,400 --> 00:20:09,599
Hey!

237
00:20:10,960 --> 00:20:12,279
You puppy,

238
00:20:12,359 --> 00:20:14,119
you're such a child.

239
00:20:15,839 --> 00:20:17,200
Dad,

240
00:20:17,279 --> 00:20:18,519
are you a BL fanboy?

241
00:20:19,200 --> 00:20:20,880
Are you crazy?

242
00:20:20,960 --> 00:20:22,720
It has to do with my case.

243
00:20:22,799 --> 00:20:25,079
You have cases like this now?

244
00:20:25,160 --> 00:20:26,519
That's pretty trendy.

245
00:20:26,599 --> 00:20:28,680
Of course.

246
00:20:28,759 --> 00:20:30,160
It's Neung's friend's case.

247
00:20:30,720 --> 00:20:31,960
I just realized

248
00:20:32,440 --> 00:20:33,759
that he's not manly.

249
00:20:35,640 --> 00:20:36,960
Not manly?

250
00:20:37,039 --> 00:20:39,039
Just the fact that he's a guy
who likes guys

251
00:20:39,119 --> 00:20:40,480
makes him not manly?

252
00:20:41,359 --> 00:20:42,920
Hey, wait,

253
00:20:44,319 --> 00:20:46,279
what do you think I mean?

254
00:20:47,039 --> 00:20:49,920
What I mean by manly is masculinity.

255
00:20:50,480 --> 00:20:52,200
A person of any gender can be manly.

256
00:20:53,079 --> 00:20:54,680
How did you understand it?

257
00:21:00,039 --> 00:21:00,960
Dad,

258
00:21:01,039 --> 00:21:02,279
keep working.

259
00:21:02,359 --> 00:21:04,240
I'll be the chef tonight.

260
00:21:04,319 --> 00:21:06,960
What do you want,
omelet, fried egg, or steamed egg?

261
00:21:07,759 --> 00:21:08,759
No thanks.

262
00:21:08,839 --> 00:21:10,839
Chef Dad will take care of it.

263
00:21:10,920 --> 00:21:12,519
Go take a shower.

264
00:21:12,599 --> 00:21:14,160
You stink. Go.

265
00:21:14,240 --> 00:21:15,680
Stink? Take that.

266
00:21:17,079 --> 00:21:19,160
Go on, you puppy.

267
00:21:20,119 --> 00:21:21,200
Oh, dear.

268
00:21:34,400 --> 00:21:36,519
Come have some fruit, Mrs. Na.

269
00:21:46,559 --> 00:21:48,039
What are you looking for?

270
00:21:50,680 --> 00:21:52,279
Saen.

271
00:21:54,519 --> 00:21:56,160
I haven't seen him.

272
00:21:56,920 --> 00:21:58,920
Did he come home last night?

273
00:22:00,440 --> 00:22:01,880
I think so.

274
00:22:02,480 --> 00:22:04,279
He probably left before you woke up.

275
00:22:04,839 --> 00:22:06,519
Right,

276
00:22:06,599 --> 00:22:08,200
I woke up late today.

277
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:11,839
I should scold him though.

278
00:22:12,440 --> 00:22:13,720
He could have woken me up.

279
00:22:16,920 --> 00:22:19,440
I don't know
how long he'll be gone this time.

280
00:22:20,079 --> 00:22:22,640
He used to work in a factory
outside Bangkok

