a birthday together.

299
00:23:34,440 --> 00:23:36,039
That's okay,

300
00:23:36,119 --> 00:23:37,880
we can celebrate together

301
00:23:37,960 --> 00:23:39,240
and make it a huge party.

302
00:23:40,319 --> 00:23:42,319
But I just had my birthday.

303
00:23:43,200 --> 00:23:44,680
But Nut's birthday

304
00:23:44,759 --> 00:23:46,079
is coming up this month.

305
00:23:47,279 --> 00:23:48,519
That's right.

306
00:23:48,599 --> 00:23:49,880
It's only a while

307
00:23:49,960 --> 00:23:51,319
until September 8.

308
00:23:52,559 --> 00:23:54,799
You know his birthday?

309
00:23:58,400 --> 00:24:00,200
He told me once.

310
00:24:04,599 --> 00:24:06,079
Nut is back.

311
00:24:25,519 --> 00:24:26,519
Hi, Mom.

312
00:24:29,680 --> 00:24:30,559
Here.

313
00:24:53,079 --> 00:24:54,559
Didn't you eat my food?

314
00:24:55,440 --> 00:24:57,640
Don't look so sad. Open it up first.

315
00:25:07,720 --> 00:25:09,960
YOURS. MOM'S.

316
00:25:11,039 --> 00:25:11,960
Tofu pudding.

317
00:25:14,240 --> 00:25:15,160
Beans in syrup.

318
00:25:20,440 --> 00:25:21,920
-Fried tofu.
-Yes.

319
00:25:22,920 --> 00:25:23,960
You got these for me?

320
00:25:24,599 --> 00:25:25,799
Can't you read?

321
00:25:27,279 --> 00:25:28,319
KEUNCHAI'S

322
00:25:28,960 --> 00:25:30,720
Keunchai's,

323
00:25:32,480 --> 00:25:33,759
Mom's,

324
00:25:35,720 --> 00:25:37,160
yours.

325
00:25:39,640 --> 00:25:40,920
Mine.

326
00:25:44,559 --> 00:25:45,720
Thank you, Nut.

327
00:25:45,799 --> 00:25:47,519
I'll finish all the tofu pudding.

328
00:25:54,279 --> 00:25:55,200
By the way,

329
00:25:55,960 --> 00:25:57,680
who gave you that pork recipe?

330
00:25:59,960 --> 00:26:01,559
I just followed my gut,

331
00:26:02,400 --> 00:26:03,240
why?

332
00:26:06,759 --> 00:26:07,799
Nothing.

333
00:26:08,359 --> 00:26:11,240
But next time, use less heat.

334
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:13,519
If I keep eating that,

335
00:26:13,599 --> 00:26:14,920
I'll get cancer.

336
00:26:15,839 --> 00:26:16,880
Okay,

337
00:26:16,960 --> 00:26:18,920
it won't be burnt next time.

338
00:26:20,319 --> 00:26:22,000
I said don't burn it.

339
00:26:22,640 --> 00:26:24,279
Yes, not burnt.

340
00:26:39,160 --> 00:26:41,000
I gathered some more evidence.

341
00:26:42,599 --> 00:26:45,799
Before Tatarn was attacked,

342
00:26:46,440 --> 00:26:49,720
apart from his co-worker,
Mrs. Sajjaree Burarat also called him.

343
00:26:50,279 --> 00:26:52,720
-That's Saen's surname.
-Yes.

344
00:26:52,799 --> 00:26:56,319
She's his wife and Tatarn's aunt.

345
00:26:57,160 --> 00:26:58,279
Isn't that odd?

346
00:26:58,839 --> 00:26:59,960
She lives in Bangkok,

347
00:27:00,039 --> 00:27:01,559
but someone saw her in Chiang Mai

348
00:27:01,640 --> 00:27:03,519
when Tatarn was attacked.

349
00:27:03,599 --> 00:27:06,640
Saen never said that his wife
was in Chiang Mai.

350
00:27:06,720 --> 00:27:09,119
It seems like he's hiding something.

351
00:27:10,359 --> 00:27:11,559
Find out

352
00:27:11,640 --> 00:27:13,960
when Sajjaree arrived and left,

353
00:27:14,039 --> 00:27:15,039
and where she went.

354
00:27:15,599 --> 00:27:16,440
Yes, sir.

355
00:27:18,599 --> 00:27:19,599
Please put that away.

356
00:27:20,319 --> 00:27:22,039
Your lieutenant called about the case?

357
00:27:23,440 --> 00:27:24,400
Yes.

358
00:27:25,519 --> 00:27:27,880
We got new evidence
in Neung's friend's case.

359
00:27:27,960 --> 00:27:28,799
So,

360
00:27:29,640 --> 00:27:31,559
do they know who did it?

361
00:27:33,880 --> 00:27:35,119
We still can't say,

362
00:27:36,359 --> 00:27:40,079
but it looks like this wasn't
a normal robbery and attack.

363
00:27:40,920 --> 00:27:43,440
Neung's friend is an activist

364
00:27:43,519 --> 00:27:45,440
and he comes from a wealthy family.

365
00:27:45,519 --> 00:27:46,839
He inherited a lot of money,

366
00:27:47,480 --> 00:27:49,559
so maybe someone is trying to harm him.

367
00:27:50,440 --> 00:27:53,920
The thing I least want to happen

368
00:27:54,640 --> 00:27:56,759
is a family conflict.

369
00:27:58,319 --> 00:27:59,519
That's true, Dad.

370
00:28:00,400 --> 00:28:02,319
If the perpetrator
is someone close to you,

371
00:28:03,119 --> 00:28:04,799
that hurts like nothing else.

372
00:28:09,599 --> 00:28:10,599
Dad,

373
00:28:10,680 --> 00:28:12,559
when do you have to get back to work?

374
00:28:13,960 --> 00:28:15,799
Tomorrow, why?

375
00:28:18,839 --> 00:28:19,799
Nothing.

376
00:28:34,839 --> 00:28:36,440
BRAT

377
00:28:37,359 --> 00:28:38,599
Brat.

378
00:28:48,720 --> 00:28:50,759
BRAT

379
00:28:56,440 --> 00:28:58,279
BRAT

380
00:29:13,680 --> 00:29:14,799
BRAT

381
00:29:17,240 --> 00:29:18,599
What is it, you imp?

382
00:29:19,880 --> 00:29:22,400
Man, you're so cold.

383
00:29:24,119 --> 00:29:26,079
Say what you have to say.

384
00:29:26,160 --> 00:29:27,200
I'm about to sleep.

385
00:29:28,720 --> 00:29:30,200
We start filming next week.

386
00:29:31,279 --> 00:29:32,119
So?

387
00:29:32,200 --> 00:29:33,680
Will I get to see you?

388
00:29:35,759 --> 00:29:36,960
I don't think so.

389
00:29:37,960 --> 00:29:39,480
But I want to see you.

390
00:29:41,799 --> 00:29:43,400
Why do you want to see me?

391
00:29:44,119 --> 00:29:45,440
Well,

392
00:29:45,519 --> 00:29:46,759
my dad is busy,

393
00:29:46,839 --> 00:29:50,200
so I want an older relative
to come and give me support.

394
00:29:51,960 --> 00:29:54,799
When did I become your relative?

395
00:29:54,880 --> 00:29:56,599
I keep treating you like an uncle

396
00:29:56,680 --> 00:29:58,480
because I wish you were my family.

397
00:29:58,559 --> 00:29:59,519
Oh,

398
00:29:59,599 --> 00:30:01,279
or should I call you

399
00:30:01,359 --> 00:30:02,559
little brother?

400
00:30:03,039 --> 00:30:05,200
You punk, brat, hoodlum,

401
00:30:05,279 --> 00:30:06,880
disrespectful crazy person!

402
00:30:07,920 --> 00:30:09,559
Now, I can sleep soundly.

403
00:30:10,359 --> 00:30:12,079
You're such a psycho.

404
00:30:12,160 --> 00:30:13,759
See you around.

405
00:30:13,839 --> 00:30:15,559
Sweet dreams. Good night.

406
00:30:15,640 --> 00:30:17,480
Kiss, kiss.

407
00:30:19,079 --> 00:30:20,400
Song, you idiot!

408
00:30:43,359 --> 00:30:46,039
I don't know why
I'm so sleepy all the time these days.

409
00:30:46,559 --> 00:30:50,400
If I didn't set three alarms,
I wouldn't have woken up.

410
00:30:51,079 --> 00:30:53,000
I think it's good to rest a lot.

411
00:30:53,079 --> 00:30:54,799
You look much stronger now,

412
00:30:55,400 --> 00:30:57,119
and more energetic during the day too.

413
00:31:02,079 --> 00:31:03,799
-Mom.
-Yes?

414
00:31:04,359 --> 00:31:07,279
We start shooting today,
so you don't need to make me lunch.

415
00:31:07,839 --> 00:31:08,759
I'll eat on the set.

416
00:31:09,799 --> 00:31:10,839
Bye now.

417
00:31:11,759 --> 00:31:13,039
Nut.

418
00:31:42,960 --> 00:31:44,319
Chu.

419
00:31:44,400 --> 00:31:45,839
-Hello.
-Hi.

420
00:31:49,200 --> 00:31:52,119
We went to the market and got you this.

421
00:31:52,200 --> 00:31:53,279
Thank you.

422
00:31:53,359 --> 00:31:54,680
-I'll hold it for you.
-What?

423
00:31:55,400 --> 00:31:57,720
It smells so good.

424
00:31:57,799 --> 00:31:59,559
Hey, listen.

425
00:32:00,319 --> 00:32:03,039
Tofu, do you know where Jan went?

426
00:32:03,119 --> 00:32:04,599
Oh,

427
00:32:04,680 --> 00:32:05,960
