428
00:32:07,279 --> 00:32:11,440
No. When I woke up this morning,
I saw her get into a taxi with a suitcase.

429
00:32:13,079 --> 00:32:14,359
She probably…

430
00:32:14,960 --> 00:32:16,720
went to see Mr. Saen in Chiang Mai.

431
00:32:17,279 --> 00:32:21,799
No wonder. They just had a fight.
She must be trying to make it up to him.

432
00:32:21,880 --> 00:32:24,119
Why are you so nosy?

433
00:32:24,680 --> 00:32:26,960
You're unbelievable.

434
00:32:27,039 --> 00:32:28,000
By the way,

435
00:32:28,079 --> 00:32:30,559
how's Na, Tofu?

436
00:32:30,640 --> 00:32:32,480
She hasn't been out to give alms lately.

437
00:32:34,160 --> 00:32:35,519
She's fine.

438
00:32:38,960 --> 00:32:39,799
Tofu,

439
00:32:41,160 --> 00:32:42,640
you know you can talk to me.

440
00:32:44,640 --> 00:32:45,759
Well…

441
00:32:47,400 --> 00:32:48,839
Mrs. Na

442
00:32:49,640 --> 00:32:52,279
hasn't been cooking for Nut.

443
00:32:53,039 --> 00:32:55,319
And she's been feeling sad

444
00:32:55,400 --> 00:32:57,359
and even blaming herself.

445
00:32:57,440 --> 00:32:59,240
She feels worthless.

446
00:32:59,799 --> 00:33:01,839
I understand her, Tofu.

447
00:33:01,920 --> 00:33:04,599
She wants to do things for her son,

448
00:33:04,680 --> 00:33:05,680
like cook for him.

449
00:33:05,759 --> 00:33:07,960
She wants to do
whatever that makes him happy.

450
00:33:08,039 --> 00:33:10,279
But now that he's a grown-up

451
00:33:10,359 --> 00:33:12,240
and he goes to work,

452
00:33:12,319 --> 00:33:14,079
she feels like

453
00:33:14,160 --> 00:33:15,319
she's not useful anymore.

454
00:33:15,400 --> 00:33:16,559
Do you understand?

455
00:33:16,640 --> 00:33:18,359
And Na is always at home.

456
00:33:19,119 --> 00:33:20,440
She never goes out.

457
00:33:20,519 --> 00:33:22,160
So now

458
00:33:22,240 --> 00:33:24,359
that she's not cooking for her son,

459
00:33:24,440 --> 00:33:26,680
she probably feels worthless.

460
00:33:28,400 --> 00:33:31,359
And what is it like
to feel you're worth something?

461
00:33:31,440 --> 00:33:32,599
Well,

462
00:33:32,680 --> 00:33:34,720
that has to do with…

463
00:33:34,799 --> 00:33:37,440
I'll let Nhong explain.
He studied engineering.

464
00:33:37,519 --> 00:33:39,839
-Nhong, explain it.
-I went to culinary school.

465
00:33:39,920 --> 00:33:42,279
Come on, explain it.

466
00:33:42,359 --> 00:33:45,559
To feel like you're worth something? Well…

467
00:33:46,519 --> 00:33:47,720
What?

468
00:33:47,799 --> 00:33:50,960
I guess it's when you make
someone else happy.

469
00:33:52,079 --> 00:33:54,599
But it doesn't have to be anything big.

470
00:33:54,680 --> 00:33:56,079
It can be small things,

471
00:33:56,160 --> 00:33:58,759
like giving them support
and making them smile.

472
00:33:58,839 --> 00:34:01,119
And you also feel happy with them.

473
00:34:01,680 --> 00:34:03,599
I guess that's the feeling

474
00:34:03,680 --> 00:34:04,839
of being worth something.

475
00:34:07,880 --> 00:34:08,960
Thank you.

476
00:34:09,039 --> 00:34:11,199
You two are worth a lot to me today.

477
00:34:11,840 --> 00:34:13,519
-Thank you.
-Hey…

478
00:34:16,079 --> 00:34:17,480
-The fried dough?
-What?

479
00:34:17,559 --> 00:34:19,719
Oh, it's so nice. Let me have one more.

480
00:34:20,559 --> 00:34:21,920
I'll be off now.

481
00:34:22,679 --> 00:34:23,880
Why did you eat it?

482
00:34:23,960 --> 00:34:25,239
We bought it for him.

483
00:34:25,880 --> 00:34:27,480
-It's for him.
-It's really good.

484
00:34:27,559 --> 00:34:29,880
How can you say that?
Why didn't you give it to him?

485
00:34:29,960 --> 00:34:31,039
Because it's good.

486
00:34:31,119 --> 00:34:33,400
-Try some.
-No.

487
00:34:34,000 --> 00:34:36,760
-It's great.
-You're so bad.

488
00:34:37,719 --> 00:34:39,480
It's really great.

489
00:34:40,960 --> 00:34:42,880
I think I understand now what it means

490
00:34:42,960 --> 00:34:44,840
to feel like you're worth something.

491
00:34:45,440 --> 00:34:47,199
When I was a teddy bear,

492
00:34:47,280 --> 00:34:48,960
I listened to Nut

493
00:34:49,039 --> 00:34:50,480
when he was happy

494
00:34:50,559 --> 00:34:52,000
and when he was sad.

495
00:34:52,079 --> 00:34:53,639
Now that I'm a person,

496
00:34:53,719 --> 00:34:56,559
I feel I'm worth even more

497
00:34:56,639 --> 00:34:58,719
because I don't just listen,

498
00:34:58,800 --> 00:35:01,360
but I can help Nut and Mrs. Na
with a lot of things.

499
00:35:01,440 --> 00:35:02,639
At least,

500
00:35:02,719 --> 00:35:05,239
I don't have to wait to be hugged anymore.

501
00:35:05,320 --> 00:35:08,880
I can hug someone
to make them feel better.

502
00:35:09,559 --> 00:35:11,800
Even though being a human isn't easy,

503
00:35:11,880 --> 00:35:14,800
I'm enjoying it more and more.

504
00:35:50,840 --> 00:35:51,880
Mrs. Na,

505
00:35:53,679 --> 00:35:55,079
shall we make some snacks?

506
00:36:13,360 --> 00:36:15,320
Do you like this location?

507
00:36:15,920 --> 00:36:17,679
The place we booked canceled on us.

508
00:36:18,880 --> 00:36:19,880
Luckily,

509
00:36:20,599 --> 00:36:22,880
my cousin is the deputy director here.

510
00:36:22,960 --> 00:36:24,159
Who?

511
00:36:24,239 --> 00:36:25,840
Joonjuea.

512
00:36:25,920 --> 00:36:29,159
Oh, hi, Pritr.

513
00:36:29,239 --> 00:36:32,559
-I would be in trouble if not for you.
-Yes.

514
00:36:32,639 --> 00:36:34,840
You never come to me
when you're not in trouble.

515
00:36:34,920 --> 00:36:36,159
Hey…

516
00:36:39,639 --> 00:36:40,519
Oh,

517
00:36:41,199 --> 00:36:42,719
aren't you Peeranut?

518
00:36:52,440 --> 00:36:56,400
This school doesn't actually accept
students in the second semester,

519
00:36:56,480 --> 00:36:58,599
but Na is my friend

520
00:36:58,679 --> 00:37:01,480
and Sib has helped me in the past,

521
00:37:01,559 --> 00:37:03,960
so I begged the director to let you in.

522
00:37:04,599 --> 00:37:05,920
Study hard

523
00:37:06,000 --> 00:37:08,000
and don't get me in trouble,

524
00:37:08,079 --> 00:37:09,400
okay?

525
00:37:09,480 --> 00:37:13,639
Don't forget that your parents asked me
to keep an eye on you.

526
00:37:23,440 --> 00:37:25,400
I thought you wouldn't remember me.

527
00:37:25,480 --> 00:37:28,679
It has been around seven to eight years
and you haven't been back once.

528
00:37:30,559 --> 00:37:32,719
Did you write the script for this series?

529
00:37:32,800 --> 00:37:34,039
What's it about?

530
00:37:38,519 --> 00:37:39,920
-Hey!
-Hey!

531
00:37:42,519 --> 00:37:45,239
About life in high school?

532
00:37:46,079 --> 00:37:48,519
You didn't use your experience
as material, right?

533
00:37:49,119 --> 00:37:50,280
Of course, I did,

534
00:37:51,360 --> 00:37:52,400
but not all of it.

535
00:37:53,760 --> 00:37:55,920
I have both good memories of this place

536
00:37:56,800 --> 00:37:57,760
and not-so-good ones

537
00:38:00,440 --> 00:38:02,400
that I personally want to tell.

538
00:38:04,360 --> 00:38:07,360
But this story isn't just about
the daily lives of kids.

539
00:38:09,079 --> 00:38:10,960
It explores society within a school,

540
00:38:12,920 --> 00:38:14,320
the class system,

541
00:38:15,360 --> 00:38:16,320
power,

542
00:38:17,199 --> 00:38:18,519
and oppression.

543
00:38:19,760 --> 00:38:21,599
Interesting.

544
00:38:22,719 --> 00:38:23,639
Does it

545
00:38:24,199 --> 00:38:26,000
also include your love story?

546
00:38:32,119 --> 00:38:33,159
Of course.

547
00:38:33,800 --> 00:38:35,519
And it's not an odd thing anymore.

548
00:38:36,039 --> 00:38:37,920
But it's still not normal.

549
00:38:41,480 --> 00:38:42,920
If for you, normal means

550
00:38:44,360 --> 00:38:45,960
only thinking the way you do,

551
00:38:47,400 --> 00:38:49,280
then half the world would be abnormal.

552
00:38:51,159 --> 00:38:52,519
For me,

553
00:38:53,719 --> 00:38:55,719
everyone is normal.

554
00:38:58,159 --> 00:38:59,760
Just because I'm not like you

555
00:39:00,559 --> 00:39:01,760
or other people

556
00:39:02,800 --> 00:39:04,679
doesn't mean that I'm not normal.

557
00:39:10,880 --> 00:39:12,559
Please watch this show once it airs.

558
00:39:13,840 --> 00:39:15,400
Maybe

559
00:39:16,239 --> 00:39:18,519
it will help you understand
sexual diversity more

560
00:39:20,039 --> 00:39:21,559
and be respectful to everyone,

561
00:39:22,800 --> 00:39:24,199
no matter their age

